reviews.content:
Taking a real gold field at Kolar, inspired by the stories of El Dorado, mixing it with the usual 'rising against all odds' narrative, a little dip here and there with 'poor vs rich', and there is a beautiful script ready. Although this cook up is not an unknown one. Several movies have already come in the past with the same concept. Nothing new here about the script. But when we put it against a mine backdrop, the dusty look, dark and shady backdrops; with lighting wherever necessary, it is this that brings out the usual story and gives it a flavour.I can give six for only this ingenious idea of filming it out of a mine setup and nice camera work and vfx to back it out. There is nothing else that is new here. A typical Indian movie with mother sentiment, copy content from here and there, put in raw masculinitiy, etc.In this 2nd chapter especially, it was more of how the protaganist fights his enemies to retain his gained empire; I would recommend here to check out Vada Chennai movie of Dhanush directed by Vetrimaaran. The director could have learnt a few lessons from there. He did bring in the guns which was influenced by Kaithi movie by Lokesh Kanagaraj but the scene felt like he wanted to force the gun there. Shoot a police station and no one is dead. Felt like too much Telugu influence also crept in. I would have been glad if the director was influenced by Malayalam or Tamil movies but Telugu movies are going to make an already larger than life story become too much extravagant;
Bringing in Sanjay Dutt did the trick with the north indian audience but not sure why he was brought in; like most of the other people who were constantly talking to each other; Instead of spending time with the already useless characters present in the movie, the government also was made the villain. Only the CIA was not in picture. May be for the next version.All big movies are coming up with good VFX but a lot of people are ignorant that its the VFX that is making them like the movie;
The director should learn the art of subte story telling and should keep game of thrones like inspired characters away and focus on the script.Have nothing to say about Yash; hearing his name first time but he did his bit in what was asked of him;
Female objectification should be avoided and raw masuculinity should be controlled; Lots of lessons to be learnt here; Hope the next version is better;
